The paper uses artificial intelligence techniques, specifically Conditional Variational Autoencoders (CVAE), to discover sustainable building materials. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI, which focuses on artificial intelligence. The paper also involves machine learning, which is a subfield of AI, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also deals with civil engineering and construction, which suggests cs.CE (Civil Engineering) and cs.SE (Software Engineering) as possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper uses open data and a web-based tool, indicating a possible connection to cs.DB (Databases).
